    "name":  "Sweet Potato Bread",
    "instructions":  "1. Preheat the oven to 175 degrees Celsius. Grease a loaf pan.\n\n2. In a large bowl, combine the sugar and oil and beat well.\n\n3. Add the egg and beat until well combined.\n\n4. In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, ground cinnamon, ground nutmeg, and salt.\n\n5. Gradually stir the flour mixture into the egg mixture, alternating with the water.\n\n6. Stir in the sweet potatoes and pecans.\n\n7. Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan.\n\n8. Bake in the preheated oven for about 1 hour, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.",
    "simpleInstructions":  "1. Preheat oven to 175 degrees Celsius and grease a loaf pan.\n\n2. Mix sugar and oil in a bowl, then add egg and beat.\n\n3. Combine flour, baking soda, ground cinnamon, ground nutmeg, and salt in another bowl.\n\n4. Gradually add dry mixture to wet, alternating with water.\n\n5. Stir in sweet potatoes and pecans.\n\n6. Pour into loaf pan and bake for 1 hour.",
